In itself, bombardier does not have an installation.

However, if you want to get some nifty statistics (variance, percentiles, std dev, and whatnot), you need to install a few packages:

In Ubuntu-based distros:

`sudo apt-get install python3-numpy python3-scipy python-matplotlib ipython ipython-notebook python-pandas python-sympy python-nose`

Otherwise, you'll just get the average response time.
